Description:
Original beauty from an era of size & quality!
Spotless, sizeable and so well located, this is a BIG opportunity for first home buyers, investors and empty-nesters alike. Set to the rear of a small group, this super-sized two bedroom unit dates from a time when space was plentiful, rooms were large and courtyard space wrapped right around. Immaculately maintained ever since, this up-sized unit features a large lounge, a huge kitchen with room for a dining setting, and a separate WC beyond a big laundry. Oversized double bedrooms are fitted with generous robes, the immaculate original bathroom stars solid terrazzo flooring...there's even a newish reverse-cycle air-conditioner for the living-room. Best of all, there's this perfect position with a prized Ormond address - ideal to leave the car in the garage and walk to Ormond and Glenhuntly station and the North Rd bus.
large lounge, huge eat-in kitchen, wrapround courtyard space, garage, robes, r/c air-con, walk to bus, tram & train

Description:
Timeless & Classic In Zone Clinker!
An old fashioned favourite, this solid brick clinker classic has been a proven performer, providing a solid base for two bedrooms, separate lounge & dining rooms, vintage bathroom (sep. bath) & kitchen, & a handy sewing/craft room or potential home office... all between traditional high ceilings & timber floors beneath existing carpeting. Extras include gas heating & a carport on 420m2/4500sqft (approx), this is an ideal start-up or downsize with potential to style-up or size-out to create an individual retreat on the border of Ormond's latte & restaurant strip, just a short stroll to neighbouring parks, in-zone McKinnon Sec. College & zone 1 station.
Solid clinker brick. 2 bedrooms with separate lounge, dining & craft room.

Location, Orientation & Accommodation!
If home is a peaceful retreat away from busy city life, then this triple fronted clinker is the perfect fit! Nestled in a quiet family-friendly street this heated & cooled three bedroom gem offers a formal lounge and dining, central kitchen with dishwasher & separate rear family room stepping out to north-facing decking amongst private & peaceful gardens where you can relax amid the birdsong, or contemplate a future extension or pool. Featuring polished boards, mirrored robes, auto lock up garage and located a short walk to Packer Park, Koornang Rd shops, schools & transport. This home offers position, privacy and potential!
Recent building and pest inspection report is available upon request.

Description:
Front up in a coveted Zone cul-de-sac
Head on up to McKinnon Hill, make your way to the very end of this coveted cul-de-sac and go to the forefront of the market with this stylish and sizeable front home. Set back beyond its own private (on-title) north-facing front garden, this two bedroom beauty will light up your life with a large northerly living wrapping around to a study space, a sun-soaked modern kitchen with glass doors to the garden and two big robe-fitted bedrooms sharing a large flexible two-way bathroom area with separate facilities. Centrally heated with air-conditioned living, even the garaging is superior with a carspace in front, auto-entry and workshop area. In the College Zone, so close to the Primary School, this one is at the forefront of Hill, College, cul-de-sac buying! Perfect investment and ideal opportunity for investors with secure tenant.

Description:
High Distinction in the Zone
This is brand new College Zone living of High Distinction. Architecturally designed to the most exacting standard, this state-of-the-art streetfront home achieves above and beyond with 37squares of living and garaging under the roofline. Appointed with every luxe finish (including Tasmanian Oak floors, CaesarStone benchtops, Emporite cabinetry and fully-tiled polished porcelain bathrooms) and every luxury appointment (including ducted heating, air-con and vacuum, video-intercom and alarm), this outstanding home ranks even higher with a 5 star Energy Rating enhanced by 6mm toughened and tinted glass, solar-hot water and LED lighting. But it takes more than appointments to top the class. From its rendered, timber-detail facade, to its flexible four bedroom plus study, three bathroom floorplan, to its expansive indoor/outdoor and first-floor living, this exceptional home is ahead of the pack. Graced with innovative design elements including ensuited bedrooms on two levels, a two-way butler's pantry for the Miele kitchen, and cornerless stacking sliders seamlessly bring the outdoors in, this standout home is at the top of the class!
living & ensuites upstairs & down, Miele kitchen, C'Stone, Emporite, Tas Oak floors, auto-gated garage, air-con, alarm, Zone address

Description:
Position! Privacy! Presentation!
Love the peaceful position offered in this triple fronted 1950s Post War property with decorative brickwork in a low traffic family-friendly neighbourhood close to schools, shops & transport! Lovingly maintained throughout, move right in & enjoy 3 generous bedrooms, formal lounge with gas log fire, formal dining room / office / potential 4th bedroom, bright family bathroom with deep bath & a gas-appliance timber kitchen overlooking meals area & spacious family room. All the comforts are here, including fresh carpets & painting, new blinds, zoned ducted heating, air-conditioning & polished boards or step outside & enjoy a private north facing rear yard - perfect for relaxing or entertaining amongst established landscaped gardens!
Gas log fire, air-con, d/heating, sun awnings, new carpets & blinds, pol. bds, paved driveway, established gardens, water tank. close to all amenities

Description:
In Zone Bungalow to Renovate or Rejuvenate!
Offered for the first time in over 40 years, this classic Californian Bungalow offers a rare opportunity to restore the perennially popular period features within and to return this gracious beauty to its former glory! Set in the heart of family-friendly Stewart St on a large allotment of 690m2 (approx), the existing two bedroom floor plan features high strapped ceilings, bay-windowed lounge, separate dining, central kitchen & a spacious sunroom overlooking deep rear gardens. Renovate or extend this charming Californian (subject to Council approval and heritage guidelines) on this McKinnon Secondary College zoned location walking distance to shops, schools & zone 1 station!
2 bedroom Cal. Bungalow in McK College zone with high ceilings, bay window & large allotment of 690m2 (approx).

Description:
Sized up, polished up, a minute to the station!
Sized up and polished up in style, this upgraded villa unit is the perfect place to step up and into the market. Showcasing a larger than usual two bedroom floorplan with separate lounge and dining rooms and an oversized master with robes and vanity area, this stylish villa unit features a quality kitchen with new stainless-steel appliances, a fresh light and bright bathroom with designer vanity and separate WC, and glossy polished boards throughout. Reverse-cycle-air-conditioned with a decorative flame heater, this quality home is even sized up outside with a generous paved and lawned wraparound courtyard, a secure garage and, out beyond the front gate, the shops and station within one block.
separate lounge & dining, updated kitchen& bathroom, sep WC, r/c air-con, flame-heater, garage, wraparound c'yard, 1 block to shops & station
